title: A systematic assessment of dissolved oxygen supply in a 20‐litre culture vessel
items.abstract: <jats:title>Abstract</jats:title><jats:p>The factors influencing aeration are discussed and, using the sulphite oxidation method of measurement, the influence of impeller diameter and speed, air rate, and air pressure on the aeration efficiency of a 20‐litre culture vessel has been determined and the power consumed by the impeller measured. Conditions are given for obtaining sulphite oxidation rates of 200–250 millimoles of O<jats:sub>2</jats:sub> per litre of medium per hour which can be increased to 500–600 millimoles by raising the operating gauge pressure from zero to 1·36 atm.</jats:p>

title: The vascular knot of the hamster uterus: The placental arterial supply and its changes during gestation and postpartum involution
The effect of oxygen supply on the rate of growth of aerobacter cloacae
items.abstract: <jats:title>Abstract</jats:title><jats:p>A simple theoretical treatment is given of the effect of a limiting oxygen supply on the growth of bacteria. Results are given for the batch culture of <jats:italic>Aerobacter cloacae.</jats:italic> Using different levels of aeration, the growth rate was measured when growth was restricted by oxygen supply. The bacterial concentration at which restriction occurred was also determined.</jats:p>
